                 "[{\"text\":\"New revelations have occurred while researching the corrupted and their habitats. It's almost as if the former person still resides within these beasts desperately trying to escape. Sometimes this can be seen in the form of delusional chatter,\"}]",
                 "[{\"text\":\"easily mistaken for attempts to communicate. Although, I have to say that whenever there is chatter the other corrupted seem to react. Some more than others, and in very rare cases they all respond equally as if they have a discussion.\"}]",
                 "[{\"text\":\"The latter only occurs when they face an event that requires above average effort to overcome.

\"}]"
               ],
               title:"The Origin Part 2",
               author:"Luthor",
               display:{Lore:["Luthor's research - Part 2"]}
             }

             {
               pages:
               [
                 "[{\"text\":\"As a scientist I feel we are on the verge of discovering something huge, something important. It's as if the corrupted have acquired a way of thinking like we do. It's nothing much just yet, but observing these mysterious grooves carved by the\"}]",
                 "[{\"text\":\"corrupted it proves they are capable of communication which implies having a memory and cognitive ability. It's something that frightens me as these findings do not appear in any of the history books. On top of that, more and more seem to\"}]",
                 "[{\"text\":\"show aberrant behavior, grouping together and moving as if they were on a journey. They all seem to move towards the outer edges of Dregora like a grand migration toward some place they're attracted to.
\"}]"
               ],
               title:"Aberrant Behavior",
               author:"Unknown",
               display:{Lore:["A research note, regarding the corrupted."]}
             }

